{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = The Most Reverend | name = Linus Nirmal Gomes |honorific-suffix =S.J. | title = Bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Baruipur|Diocese of Baruipur]] (emeritus) | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Baruipur|The Diocese of Baruipur]] | term = 1977 - 1995 | predecessor = none | successor = Salvadore Lobo<!-- Orders --> | ordination = 21 November 1954 | consecration = 30 April 1977 | consecrated_by = Archbishop [[Eugene Louis D’Souza]] | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1921|9|7}} | birth_place = [[Boro Golla]], [[India]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]] | previous_post = | ordinated_by = }}
'''Linus Nirmal Gomes''' (born 7 September 1921) is an [[India]]n [[Society of Jesus|Jesuit]] priest, elected in 1977 bishop of the newly established diocese of Baruipur. He retired in 1995.
Gomes was born in Boro Golla (India), joined the [[Society of Jesus]] on 26 June 1942, and was ordained a [[Catholic priest|priest]] on 21 November 1954. Gomes was appointed bishop to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Baruipur|Diocese of Baruipur]] on 30 May 1977 and ordained bishop on 19 November 1977. Gomes retired on 31 October 1995 as bishop of the Baruipur Diocese.
