The '''Human Rights and Minorities Affairs Department''' is a [[Ministry (government department)|department]] of the [[Government of Punjab, Pakistan]]. The department is responsible for protection and safeguarding the [[fundamental human rights]] without any distinction of creed, race or religion. The department also refers and recommends investigations and inquiries in case of any violation of human rights.<ref>[http://punjab.gov.pk/human_rights_and_minorities_affairs_department Human Rights and Minorities Affairs Department | Punjab Portal<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Administration of minorities affairs is done under The Christian Marriage Act 1872 and [http://punjablaws.gov.pk/laws/41.html The Hindu Gains of Learning Act 1930].
